article.headline: Liberty 92, Radford 85
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Seth Curry scored 25 points and Kyle Ohman added 24 as Liberty defeated Radford 92-85 on Saturday night, snapping the Highlanders' nine-game winning streak despite Artsiom Parakhouski's career-high 39 points plus 19 rebounds. The Flames (21-10, 12-6 Big South Conference) ended a two-game skid in the regular-season finale for both teams and avenged a 94-82 overtime loss to the Highlanders (18-11, 15-3) on Jan. 24. With Liberty ahead 45-33 at halftime, Parakhouski scored six of his 25 second-half points to make it 47-41 with 16:53 left. Curry hit a 3-pointer and Radford, which had won 14 of its previous 15 games, could get no closer than six the rest of the way. Liberty made 18 of 24 free throws in the final 3:06. Parakhouski went 15 of 19 from the field and 9 of 16 from the free-throw line. Kenny Thomas added 23 points for the Highlanders.
